# Migrate Storage from SQLite to PostgreSQL

The Vercel serverless environment has a **read-only filesystem**, so SQLite cannot persist data. The fix is to replace `sqlite3` with `psycopg2` and point it to a free PostgreSQL database (Neon, Supabase, or Vercel Postgres). The connection string is supplied via an environment variable — no credentials in code.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **You will need a free PostgreSQL database URL before the app can run.**
> Recommended: [Neon](https://neon.tech) (free tier, serverless Postgres, works great with Vercel).
> After creating a database, copy the connection string — it looks like:
> `postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require`
> Set it as `DATABASE_URL` in your Vercel project's Environment Variables.

## Proposed Changes

### Storage Layer

#### [MODIFY] [logic.py](file:///d:/Coding/Python/CS50/Projects/smart_expense_tracker/web/logic.py)

- Remove all `sqlite3` imports and DB-file path config
- Add `DATABASE_URL = os.environ["DATABASE_URL"]` (raises a clear error if not set)
- Replace `_get_connection()` with a `psycopg2.connect(DATABASE_URL)` helper using `RealDictCursor` (returns rows as dicts automatically)
- Replace SQLite `?` placeholders with `%s` (psycopg2 standard)
- Replace `INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT` with `SERIAL PRIMARY KEY` in `CREATE TABLE`
- Keep `init_db()`, all CRUD functions, `get_summary()`, `filter_by_category()` — same signatures, same return types
- Remove `_migrate_legacy_json()` — not applicable on serverless

